track_notes: The path leads to 3 summits, look at the single and carry on to the multiple!

Nice walk to the summit, you need to be healthy and have good shoes, in winter there is snow at the end, may be snowshoes are fine; the panorama is wonderfull and much room for antennas.
One or two places for cars!
From the village of Bairols, very long walk for 2 six pointer summits. Parking is ok at the village

New trace, easier in my opinion, parking available (3 places) on the road, access to the secondary road is restricted to cars, ok for walkers. Several tracks available on the way, better using a GPS, especially in the forest as the path is not easy to follow. Cows on the tracks :-)
